column5: Been blessed with awsome weather, good friends to be with in the new year, and most of all... time! having come back from my holiday trip i find out that i dont work until this up coming sunday, we all know what that means!  my first fish of the year! haha   mikes(dozer) beauty female   this fish must have gotten itself caught on some netting of some sort, it was not wrapped in my line at all. it took me less that 15 seconds to get him to shore to release him.   then my first big boy of the year decided to come out n play,    hope everyone else is having a great beginning to the new year!
looks like you had a great day!  too bad i'm stuck at work .... gotta christen the new-to-me islander soonnnn
Congrats very nice pictures!!!
thanks, hey vic are u grabbing anthonys set up? or kelvins green islander? hahah
holy crap. very very nice fish. keep up the good work.
Good stuff, love the black n white pic, with the snow n the weird tree...
Damn man...your first fish of 2011 beats mine.... a 6" perch  Nice work!
haha thanks dude, i heard about your new toy  get to use it just yet?
I got a black one used. Don't really like the green and gold's too blingbling for me.
*SMILES*
Very nice steelies! What happened to the one in the second picture? It looks like part of it's gill plate is missing.

pretty cheap actually, im a one man team haha.  thanks guys, i dont know exactly what causes the gill plate deformation. ive seen many fish over the years with the same problem and have heard many theories but none ever proven. either way they all seem to be healthy fish.
Great post and nice fish!
Those are some nice fish indeed! Congrats on a great start to 2011.
Good open for 2011  nice job
I think it's time you put them wicked camera skills to use on the Ice. If you're ever interested I know a few good guides that you already know!
Nicely done! What Great Lake does that Trib belong to??  Those are some beauties.
Gorgious all around. Sure beats my perch as well
Nice Bro!! We need to go fishing soon!! Finally ordered WFN!
the trib runs into lake ontario, hey jet me and kelvin hit cooks bay a couple days ago!  rob, let me know when your free, we should hit some ice fishin up!
cheeee yeah
